text:
How to Use Spotify - Beginner's Guide

Spotify is a music streaming platform with over 50 million songs that you can listen to any time on demand.

Spotify is available on Spotify.com and on mobile and desktop apps for iOS, Android, Mac, and PC.

There are two versions of Spotify.  A free version supported by ads and you can only skip a few songs at a time. 

And there is a paid version starting at $10 a month that is ad-free and you can also skip as many songs as you like.
You can also listen offline by downloading them, meaning you don't need an internet connection to stream the music.  
There are also options for family and students.

The Spotify platform will get to know you over time and recommend music to you as you use the app more.

Inside of the Spotify app, you can create playlists and much more that we will cover in this video.

Thank you for watching this video! Please share and subscribe for more, easy to follow social media and tech videos.

Questlove also divulges to Trevor the names of all 432 people who get his weekly playlist (no he doesn’t) and reveals all the celebrities who come to his legendary game nights (he doesn’t reveal that either but it’s still a fantastic conversation).

WHAT NOW? WITH TREVOR NOAH
Hear Trevor Noah in a way you’ve never heard him before. “What Now? with Trevor Noah” is a show wherein each episode Trevor will go deep with a special guest, including entertainers, CEOs, actors, athletes, and thought leaders. These are the kind of conversations that happen behind the scenes, full of radical candor, authentic back-and-forths, and honest reactions, with Trevor bringing to bear his classic, effortlessly playful and equally probing style. Produced by Spotify Studios in partnership with Day Zero Productions and Fulwell 73.

SPOTIFY
Spotify’s platform revolutionized music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our move into podcasting brought innovation and a new generation of listeners to the medium, and in 2022 we entered the next audio market primed for growth with the addition of audiobooks.

Today, more listeners than ever can discover, manage, and enjoy over 100 million tracks, 5 million podcasts titles, and 350,000 audiobooks a la carte on Spotify. Spotify’s platform revolutionized music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our move into podcasting brought innovation and a new generation of listeners to the medium, and in 2022 we entered the next audio market primed for growth with the addition of audiobooks.

Today, more listeners than ever can discover, manage, and enjoy over 100 million tracks, 5 million podcasts titles, and 350,000 audiobooks a la carte on Spotify.
